      • getValue

        public List<Map<String,String>> getValue(String elementPath)
        Get the List, containing value of the Socket Element or Socket Elements with their attributes specified by elementPath. Element Path can be any of the following. (1) elementId (e.g. eltId) (2) path from root(e.g. /set1/set2[index1]/id) (3) path for range of indices(e.g. /set1/set2[index1 index5]/id, /set1/set2[index1]/id[]) (4) root (e.g. /) Return the List of Map of element Path from the root, its value and attributes. Map doesn't contain the value of sets and its child Elements(Applicable only in case of set path and root path).
        Parameters:
        elementPath - a String value of elementPath
        Returns:
        an Object of List<Map<String, String>> representing paths,its value and attributes.

      • getValue

        public List<Map<String,String>> getValue(String elementPath,
                                         boolean includeSets)
        Get the List, containing value of the Socket Element or Socket Elements with their attributes specified by elementPath. Element Path can be any of the following. (1) elementId (e.g. eltId) (2) path from root(e.g. /set1/set2[index1]/id) (3) path for range of indices(e.g. /set1/set2[index1 index5]/id, /set1/set2[index1]/id[]) (4) root (e.g. /) If the value of includeSets is true, then get the value child sets recursively. Else don't include set in return Map. includeSets is applicable to only Sets and root not any other Socket Elements. Return the List of Map of element Path from the root, its value and attributes.
        Parameters:
        elementPath - a String value of elementPath
        Returns:
        an Object of List<Map<String, String>> representing paths,its value and attributes

      • setValue

        public int setValue(String elementPath,
                    String value)
        Set the value of Specified Socket Element by elementPath. The element path must be for single socket element. If value of specified socket element set successfully then returns int value 0(SUCCESSFUL). If specified elementPath is invalid or such a Socket Element does not exists then returns int value 1(INCORRECT_PATH); If specified elementPath has invalid dimension value then returns int value 2(INCORRECT_DIM_VALUE).
        Parameters:
        elementPath - String elementPath a String value of Element Path.
        value - a String
        Returns:
        an int value representing whether the value is set successfully or not.

      • addDimension

        public int addDimension(String elementPath,
                        String value)
        Add new Dimension to the Dimensional IUISocketElement specified by 'elementPath'. If dimension is added successfully then returns int value 0(SUCCESSFUL). If specified elementPath is invalid or such a Socket Element does not exists then returns int value 1(INCORRECT_PATH); If specified elementPath has invalid dimension value then returns int value 2(INCORRECT_DIM_VALUE). If the dimension specified by elementPath is already exists then return int value 3(DIMENSION_ALREADY_EXISTS).
        Parameters:
        elementPath - a String value of elementPath
        value - a String value
        Returns:
        whether Dimension has been added successfully or not.

      • removeDimension

        public int removeDimension(String elementPath)
        Remove the existing Dimension of the Dimensional IUISocketElement specified by 'elementPath'. If dimension is removed successfully then returns int value 0(SUCCESSFUL). If specified elementPath is invalid or such a Socket Element does not exists then returns int value 1(INCORRECT_PATH); If specified elementPath has invalid dimension value then returns int value 2(INCORRECT_DIM_VALUE).
        Parameters:
        elementPath - a String value of elementPath
        Returns:
        whether Dimension is removed successfully or not
